svg:text.svg:tspan: In the exam, you’ll be given one poem from the cluster and will be asked to compare it with another poem
of your choice from the cluster. You’ll usually be asked to compare the poems based on a theme.
You need to choose a second poem that has similar themes to the first. This table shows the major themes
for each poem in the cluster — make sure they’re as clear as possible in your head, so when you get into
the exam you don’t waste time trying to work out which poems might be suitable.
